          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-06-12T19:20:07Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Conservation Reserve Enhancement Program Improvement Act of 2018 </b></p> <p>This bill modifies and provides statutory authority for the Department of Agriculture (USDA) Conservation Reserve Enhancement Program (CREP). </p> <p>CREP is a subprogram of the Conservation Reserve Program (CRP), under which USDA partners with states to target high-priority conservation concerns, and the states contribute funding to allow for higher CRP payments and continuous sign-ups to address the concerns. </p> <p>The bill directs USDA, to the maximum extent practicable, to enroll at least 3 million acres of land in CREP by September 30, 2023. </p>]]></text>
        </item>
